    "trap_detected": "Calculation Error",
    "explanation_english": "The word 'QUESTION' has 8 distinct letters: Q, U, E, S, T, I, O, N.\nNumber of Vowels (V): U, E, I, O (4 vowels)\nNumber of Consonants (C): Q, S, T, N (4 consonants)\nWe need to select 5 letters such that at least two vowels are included.\nThis means we can have the following combinations of vowels and consonants:\n\nCase 1: 2 Vowels and 3 Consonants\nNumber of ways to choose 2 vowels from 4 = C(4, 2) = (4 × 3) / (2 × 1) = 6\nNumber of ways to choose 3 consonants from 4 = C(4, 3) = 4\nTotal ways for Case 1 = C(4, 2) × C(4, 3) = 6 × 4 = 24\n\nCase 2: 3 Vowels and 2 Consonants\nNumber of ways to choose 3 vowels from 4 = C(4, 3) = 4\nNumber of ways to choose 2 consonants from 4 = C(4, 2) = 6\nTotal ways for Case 2 = C(4, 3) × C(4, 2) = 4 × 6 = 24\n\nCase 3: 4 Vowels and 1 Consonant\nNumber of ways to choose 4 vowels from 4 = C(4, 4) = 1\nNumber of ways to choose 1 consonant from 4 = C(4, 1) = 4\nTotal ways for Case 3 = C(4, 4) × C(4, 1) = 1 × 4 = 4\n\nTotal number of ways = Sum of ways from all cases = 24 + 24 + 4 = 52.",
